5|$|Observances of State {{mourning}} on {{the death}} of foreign dignitaries are governed by special instructions issued from the Ministry of Home Affairs in individual cases. However, in the event of death of either the Head of the State or Head of the Government of a foreign country, the Indian Mission accredited to that country may fly the national <b>flag</b> <b>at</b> <b>half-mast.</b>|$|E
25|$|The Department {{provides}} a subscription-based email service called the Commonwealth Flag Network, which gives information on national occasions {{to fly the}} <b>flag</b> <b>at</b> <b>half-mast</b> as well as national days of commemoration and celebration of the flag.|$|E
